vital signs within normal limits. A CT scan is arranged (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Simple liver cyst","Hepatocellular carcinoma","Metastatic deposit","Empyema of the gallbladder","Hydatid cyst"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThere is a large cystic structure in the right lobe of the liver, occupying most of segments IV and VIII. The cyst contents are homogenous and there is a rim of calcification around the cyst. These are the typical features associated with an \u003Cstrong\u003Ehydatid cyst\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHydatid cysts are the result of infection with \u003Cem\u003EEchinococcus granulosus\u003C/em\u003E. The dog is the primary host and grazing animals (sheep, cattle) are the intermediate hosts. Man becomes an inadvertent intermediate host through the ingestion of eggs shed in dog faeces. This form of tapeworm is endemic in Australia and was introduced in to this country with sheep farming. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst hydatid disease used to be a relatively common condition in sheep grazing regions (New South Wales and Victoria), with the introduction of dog-deworming and improved hand hygiene, the disease is now seen infrequently. Cyst formation is usually in the liver, and other sites include the lungs and spleen. The cysts are most often solitary and found incidentally, but depending on their size can produce symptoms - as in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst on the size alone, it could be a \u003Cstrong\u003Esimple liver cyst,\u003C/strong\u003E the rim of calcification excludes such a diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary tumours (eg. hepatocellular carcinoma) \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003Emetastatic deposits \u003C/strong\u003Ewould not be cystic and even if there was a cystic component, the neoplastic lesion would be heterogenous.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe lesion is within the liver and so cannot be the gallbladder. If this was an \u003Cstrong\u003Eempyema of the gallbladder,\u003C/strong\u003E the patient would almost certainly have had some systemic symptoms suggestive of an acute infection.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hydatid cysts are uncommon outside the regions of the world where the disease is endemic."],"references":["Higuita NIA, Brunetti E, McLoskey C. Cystic Echinococcosis. J Clin Microbiol 2016; 54:518-23. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26677245/","Keong B, Wilkie B, Sutherland T, et al. Hepatic cystic echinococcosis in Australia: an update on diagnosis and management. ANZ J Surg. 2018;88:26-31. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29024292/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76055"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1356"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16294"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16294","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16294"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0635d0c2-dee0-437e-b1a5-1b01fddc04de.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0635d0c2-dee0-437e-b1a5-1b01fddc04de.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":555,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76055","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76055"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-18T21:03:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-18T21:05:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1356"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92694"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"r